Professional Staff Congress/City University of New York Records

Contents

Series I: Records of the United Federation of College Teachers, 1935-1972

langmaterial

English

Scope and Content Note

Series I: Records of the United Federation of College Teachers, includes Executive Board minutes (1963-1972), files on individual campuses and categories of CUNY employees, correspondence, extensive files on grievances (many arranged alphabetically by name), Negotiating Committee files, mass mailings to members, publicity materials, and material relating to the new York State College and University Council of the American Federation of Teachers.

Series II: Records of the Legislative Conference, 1926-1975

langmaterial

English

Scope and Content Note

Series II: Records of the Legislative Conference, includes minutes (1938-1972), files on individual campuses, files relating to the Board of Higher Education, documentation of relations with CUNY administrators, officers' correspondence, legislative issues files, documentation on the struggle for collective bargaining representation, files on salaries, and extensive documentation of the activities of LC president Belle Zeller.

Series III: Records of the Professional Staff Congress, 1926-2016

langmaterial

English

Scope and Content Note

Series III: Records of the Professional Staff Congress, includes constitutions, minutes (1972-1997), biographical files on officers and staff, files on individual chapters, CUNY budget files, extensive documentation of the New York City fiscal crisis of the mid-1970s, general correspondence, election files, publicity materials, lobbying files, and a series of files on PSC history. Also included are reference files on issues of concern to the union, such as affirmative action, open admissions, tenure quotas, collective bargaining in higher education, sex discrimination, and the role of students in university affairs. An extensive sub-series is comprised of office files of individual officers and staff members, including Aaron Alexander, Claude Campbell, Irwin Polishook, Irwin Yellowitz and Belle Zeller. Another sub-series is devoted to benefits-related files, including records of the Welfare Fund, the Pension Committee and Retirement Planning programs, as well as correspondence of staff members Clarissa Weiss and Beryl Weinberg. Also included are reference files on issues of concern to the union such as affirmative action, open admissions, tenure quotas, collective bargaining in higher education, sex discrimination, and the role of students in university affairs.

Series V: Addendum, 1957-2004

langmaterial

English

Scope and Content Note

Series V: Addendum, is comprised mostly of material donated by the union in 2006 after its headquarters was moved from 25 West 43rd St. in New York City. The series consists of six sub-series, as follows: A. Minutes, 1970-2004, including minutes of Delegate Assembly and Executive Council meetings; B. Correspondence, 1976-2000, including incoming and outgoing correspondence of Frank Annunziato, Barbara Bowen, Arnold Cantor, and Irwin Polishook; C. Bargaining Files, 1969-1995; D. City University of New York (CUNY), Budget and General Files, 1973-1999, including incoming and outgoing correspondence with CUNY officials, reports, budget materials, clippings and publicity material covering all aspects of the PSC's relationship with the CUNY system; E. Clarion Files, 1974-2000, including drafts of articles, editorial correspondence and background materials used in the production of the union's newspaper; F. General Files, 1957-2004, comprised of subject files on topics, organizations, persons and issues of concern to the union. Also included in this series are the files of the Belle Zeller Scholarship Fund, files on the PSC's relations with the American Association of University Professors (AAUP) and with the American Federation of Teachers, and extensive files documenting the activities of PSC chapters on the many campuses of the CUNY system.

Series VII: Photographs and Audiovisual Materials, 1960s-1999

Scope and Content Note

Series VII: Photographs and Audiovisual Materials, contains photographs, negatives, and contact sheets related to faculty and PSC chapters at various campuses, as well as CUNY programs and administration, PSC affiliate groups, PSC officers, and PSC meetings and events. This series also includes some audiovisual materials.

Arrangement

Most of this series maintains the original arrangement of the photographs by Aaron Alexander, former Associate Executive Director of PSC.

Photographs, Contact Sheets, and Negatives re: Administration (CUNY), Admission Services (CUNY), Affiliate: AUP (American Association of University Professors, Affiliate: AFT (American Federation of Teachers), Affiliate: NYSUT (New York State United Teachers), Affiliate: UFT (United Federation of Teachers), Affiliate: United University Professions (SUNY), Alumni (CUNY), Arbitrators AAA, B.A. Program, Baruch College Faculty, Baruch NCSCBHEP, Baruch PSC Chapter, Board of Trustees- Board of Higher Education (CUNY), Bronx Community Faculty, and Bronx PSC Chapter, 1970s-1980s

(CUNY), Central Office Chapter, Chancellors Reception for Scholars/Distinguished Professors (CUNY), City College Faculty, City College NY-PSC Chapter, Computer Center (CUNY), Committee for Public Higher Education, Conferences- PSC, Delegate Assembly- PSC, Educational Opportunity Center (CUNY), Emergency Financial Control Board (CUNY), Faculty Development, Florida Chapter- PSC, General Equivalency Diploma (CUNY), Graduate School Faculty, and Graduate School PSC Chapter, 1970s-1980s

31142063584745box: 236 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Series VIII: Archived Websites,

Extent

2 websites in 2 archived websites.

Scope and Contents

This series contains the website for the Professional Staff Congress, dating back to 2007. The website is made up of news and updates from the union, information about their welfare fund, current contract and contract negotiations information, calendar of events, photo galleries, rights as a union member, committee information, benefits for part-timers and retirees, professional development, campaigns and political action information, and their newsletter "Clarion." From late 2012-2015, the website was unsuccessfully captured.

The PSC archive is the website of the City University of New York Professional Staff Congress, which is no longer active but has been maintained for posterity as an archival resource by CUNY. The site features back issues of the PSC newspaper "The Clarion", information about the organizational structure of the PSC including chapters and committees, the PSC contract, benefits information, dues information, grievances and rights information, a photo gallery, statements about official political and legislative stances of the PSC, news, salary schedules, and staff and officers' profiles.

Accruals

New site crawls are accrued semiannually.

Appraisal

Crawl was limited to domains and subdomains of psc-cuny.org, archive.psc-cuny.org, and staging.psc-cuny.org in order to remain within the collection scope and data constraints.

Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements

Due to technical or privacy issues, archived websites may not be exact copies of the original website at the time of the web crawl. Certain file types will not be captured dependent on how they are embedded in the site. Other parts of websites that the crawler has difficulty capturing includes Javascript, streaming content, database-driven content, and highly interactive content. Full-Text searches of archived websites are available at https://archive-it.org/organizations/567.
